1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,760
This is MakeYour, one iPhone app

2
00:00:02,760 --> 00:00:05,990
where GPT-5.6 creates
the tiny apps you need.

3
00:00:06,100 --> 00:00:08,550
My Apps keeps every creation.

4
00:00:08,650 --> 00:00:11,450
Builder is where you create
or change them.

5
00:00:11,550 --> 00:00:16,450
AI Key connects your own OpenAI key
and GPT-5.6.

6
00:00:16,550 --> 00:00:20,400
Together, they become one home
for your personal tiny apps.

7
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:26,880
Now I ask GPT-5.6 for TripPilot,
a three-page travel command center with currency,

8
00:00:27,280 --> 00:00:32,860
budget, itinerary, device tools, and AI.
This is the real generation run; only the

9
00:00:32,860 --> 00:00:36,940
waiting time is accelerated. The first
document fails semantic validation.

10
00:00:37,560 --> 00:00:42,220
Instead of timing out or asking me to
start over, MakeYour keeps my prompt,

11
00:00:42,220 --> 00:00:48,400
sends precise diagnostics back to GPT-5.6
and automatically repairs revision one.

12
00:00:48,400 --> 00:00:53,560
After capability review, the validated app
opens with 31 native components and 21 reviewed

13
00:00:53,560 --> 00:00:59,760
capabilities. Its generated converter works too:
100 U.S. dollars becomes 3,250

14
00:00:59,760 --> 00:01:04,580
Taiwan dollars. That entire interface came
from the prompt, not a hard-coded

15
00:01:04,580 --> 00:01:05,320
TripPilot template.

16
00:01:06,800 --> 00:01:09,100
A useful app should also feel like yours.

17
00:01:09,550 --> 00:01:11,700
I complete a task, return to Builder,

18
00:01:11,700 --> 00:01:14,900
and ask for a calm green design
with a short evening reflection.

19
00:01:15,600 --> 00:01:19,300
GPT-5.6 creates Version 3
with a new style and a new feature,

20
00:01:19,300 --> 00:01:22,400
while my completed task is still there.

21
00:01:22,700 --> 00:01:25,550
The app changes with me,
without starting over.

22
00:01:25,800 --> 00:01:28,200
Back in My Apps, Daily Focus

23
00:01:28,200 --> 00:01:30,200
is only one of many.

24
00:01:30,400 --> 00:01:33,300
I can switch to a travel budget
converter,

25
00:01:33,300 --> 00:01:35,850
live currency alerts,
or a private food journal.

26
00:01:36,100 --> 00:01:39,600
Every tiny app can have
its own interface, capabilities, and data,

27
00:01:39,600 --> 00:01:43,100
while they all live inside MakeYour.

28
00:01:43,400 --> 00:01:45,000
No new Xcode project.

29
00:01:45,200 --> 00:01:46,800
No separate build pipeline.

30
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:48,650
No starting from scratch.

31
00:01:48,900 --> 00:01:52,500
Codex helped us build and test
the schema, validator,

32
00:01:52,550 --> 00:01:56,850
safety boundary, and native SwiftUI
runtime that make this possible.

33
00:01:57,100 --> 00:02:00,000
The next tiny app you need
is one prompt away.

34
00:02:00,400 --> 00:02:01,100
One app.

35
00:02:01,450 --> 00:02:02,650
Your tiny apps.

36
00:02:02,800 --> 00:02:03,750
Make yours.
